race.comment: NORTH TERRACE (2) followed up a nice return from a let-up two back with a game maiden win over this trip at Kembla last Saturday, coming from next to last on the bend to just arrive in time. Trained here and can go on with the job now. On-pacer HERON (6) has looked a winning chance at some stage of her last four runs but has been overwhelmed late on each occasion. The mile looks her right trip, with a couple of recent placings to her name. Looks to get her own way here and might be tough to reel in. PERFECT JUSTICE (1) worked through the line well to get up for third when resuming over 1500m here a fortnight ago. Finds the ideal race at this stage of the prep. Should roll forward from a wide alley and give backers a sight. CHANNELLING (3) couldn't quicken over 1200m when fresh from a spell at Kembla recently. Locally trained mare who might enjoy this step up in distance. THINK ROMANCE (7) wasn't far away following a one-month let-up last start. Each-way hope.
